\begin_layout Section
Physics analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In high energy and astroparticle physics physicists are often confronted
 with a large amount of data to handle and analyze.
 The performed analysis can also become very complex.
 This is where the common term 'physics analysis' appears.
 For an introductory example, I present in figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Feyman-graph:Z0"

\end_inset

 the feyman diagram of the simple reaction 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{+}e^{-}\rightarrow Z^{0}\rightarrow\mu^{+}\mu^{-}$
\end_inset

 which can takes place at the interaction point in a particle accelerator.
\end_layout

