\begin_layout Standard
The following advantages of a browser based application against a local
 application/own programed analysis makes this concept very attractive for
 physics analysis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
There is no need for an operating system based installation on the client.
 Only a web browser with support for Web 2.0
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The concrete support for a feature is specified in the supporting HTML standard
 of a browser.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 is required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The user needs no administrator rights to run a new application.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
A application runs on the client with only the front-end.
 The back-end runs on the server.
 Therefore, the application uses the server computing resources and becomes
 independent of the client's computer hardware/environment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In my thesis, I will demonstrate, how these new technologies can be used
 for developing a graphical physics analysis environment as a web application
 and how to perform a physics analysis with it.
\end_layout

